@startuml
skinparam MinClassWidth 120
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam packageMargin 20
skinparam nodesep 80
skinparam ranksep 80
title PartyRole - Type-Instance Pattern (Recommended, Annotated)

' ===== PARTY BASE =====
package "Core Party Archetype" {
  object Party
  object Person
  object Organization

  Person -up-|> Party
  Organization -up-|> Party
}

' ===== PARTY ROLE TYPE - CATALOG =====
package "PartyRoleType - Catalog" #CCCCFF {
  object PartyRoleType {
    id: PartyRoleTypeId
    name: String
    description: String
  }

  object PartyRoleConstraint {
    isSatisfiedBy(Party): boolean
  }

  PartyRoleType "1" *-- "1..*" PartyRoleConstraint
}

' ===== PARTY ROLE - INSTANCE =====
package "PartyRole - Instance" #FFCCCC {
  object PartyRole {
    partyId: PartyId
  }

  PartyRole "0..*" -- "1" PartyRoleType : instance of
  Party "1" -- "0..*" PartyRole : plays
}

note right of PartyRoleType
  <b>PartyRoleType = Catalog</b>
  (like ProductType)

  Defined once, used many times:
  - EMPLOYEE (only Person)
  - EMPLOYER (only Organization)
  - CUSTOMER (any Party)
  - MANAGER (only Person)

  Managed via API:
  - Add new types at runtime
  - Update descriptions
  - Modify constraints
  - No code changes needed

  Benefits:
  ✓ No String chaos
  ✓ Rich metadata
  ✓ Validation via constraints
  ✓ Runtime flexibility
  ✓ Reporting (list all types)
  ✓ Multi-tenant support
end note

note right of PartyRole
  <b>PartyRole = Instance</b>
  (like ProductInstance)

  Concrete role of specific Party:
  - John plays EMPLOYEE
  - Acme plays EMPLOYER
  - Jane plays MANAGER

  Many instances share same type:
  - 1000 employees → 1 EMPLOYEE type
  - Metadata stored once in type
  - No duplication

  Type-Instance pattern:
  PartyRoleType (1) → PartyRole (*)
end note

note bottom of PartyRoleConstraint
  <b>Constraints in Catalog</b>

  Define who can play role:
  - onlyPerson()
  - onlyOrganization()
  - anyParty()
  - minimumAge(18)
  - requiresCertification(...)

  Validated automatically:
  Organization cannot be EMPLOYEE
  Person cannot be EMPLOYER
end note

note bottom of Party
  <b>Type-Instance Pattern</b>

  Same as Product archetype:

  ProductType → ProductInstance
  PartyRoleType → PartyRole

  One type definition,
  many instances.
end note

@enduml
